description: Quebec Precious Metals Corporation engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mining projects in Canada. The company explores for gold, silver, copper, nickel, and zinc deposits. Its flagship project is the Sakami Gold project comprising a block of 281 contiguous mineral claims covering an area of 142.5 square kilometers located in the Northwest of Montreal. The company was incorporated in 1984 and is headquartered in Montreal, Canada.
ceo: Mr. Normand  Champigny Ing., M.A.Sc., P.Eng.
